      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Moshe Koppel</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Moshe_Koppel.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Moshe_Koppel.jpg/330px-Moshe_Koppel.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"361\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/33/Moshe_Koppel.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Moshe_Koppel.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Moshe Koppel <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Moshe Koppel</b>,<br />\nan American-Israeli computer scientist, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talmud\">Talmud</a> scholar and professor at the Department of Computer Science, <a href=\"/Bar-Ilan_University\" title=\"Bar-Ilan University\">Bar-Ilan University</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramat_Gan\">Ramat-Gan</a>. \nHe received the Ph.D. degree for his work in logic and number theory from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_University\">New York University</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. \nHis research interests includes <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">machine learning</a> and its application to problems related to the automated <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Content_analysis\">analysis of texts</a>. Along with <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Eli David</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> and <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, Moshe Koppel worked and published on <a href=\"/Genetic_Programming#GeneticAlgorithm\" title=\"Genetic Programming\">Genetic Algorithms</a> in computer chess.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1980_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1980 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Moshe_Koppel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1980_...\">1980 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Moshe_Koppel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1980 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>1980</b>). <i>Bases of Recursively Enumerable Relations</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_University\">New York University</a>, advisor <a href=\"/Mathematician#MDDavis\" title=\"Mathematician\">Martin D. Davis</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://bruce.edmonds.name/combib/compref197.html\">Complexity, Depth, and Sophistication</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_Systems_(journal)\">Complex Systems</a>, Vol. 1, No. 6, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://wpmedia.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/13/2018/02/01-6-4.pdf\">pdf</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1016/0097-3165%2889%2990089-7\">Unpredictable strings are collectives</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Combinatorial_Theory\">Journal of Combinatorial Theory</a>, Series A, Vol. 51, No. 1</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Moshe_Koppel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/f/Feldman:Ronen\">Ronen Feldman</a>, <a href=\"/Alberto_Maria_Segre\" title=\"Alberto Maria Segre\">Alberto Maria Segre</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BkN3AjbdWB\">Incremental Refinement of Approximate Domain Theories</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icml/ml1991.html\">ML 1991</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/f/Feldman:Ronen\">Ronen Feldman</a>, <a href=\"/Alberto_Maria_Segre\" title=\"Alberto Maria Segre\">Alberto Maria Segre</a> (<b>1994</b>). <i>Bias-Driven Revision of Logical Domain Theories</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research</a>, Vol. 1, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/cs/9402103\">arXiv:cs/9402103</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shlomo_Argamon\">Shlomo Argamon-Engelson</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Tractability of Theory Patching</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research</a>, Vol. 8, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/cs/9803103\">arXiv:cs/9803103</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Moshe_Koppel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Genetic Algorithms for Mentor-Assisted Evaluation Function Optimization</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sigevo.org/gecco-2008/\">GECCO '08</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.06839\">arXiv:1711.06839</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://u.cs.biu.ac.il/~schlerj/\">Jonathan Schler</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shlomo_Argamon\">Shlomo Argamon</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>Computational Methods in Authorship Attribution</i>. JASIST, 60, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://u.cs.biu.ac.il/~koppel/papers/authorship-JASIST-final.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shlomo_Argamon\">Shlomo Argamon</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_W._Pennebaker\">James W. Pennebaker</a>,  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://u.cs.biu.ac.il/~schlerj/\">Jonathan Schler</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>Automatically Profiling the Author of an Anonymous Text</i>. <a href=\"/ACM#Communications\" title=\"ACM\">Communications of the ACM</a>, Vol. 52, No. 2, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://u.cs.biu.ac.il/~koppel/papers/AuthorshipProfiling-cacm-final.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>Simulating Human Grandmasters: Evolution and Coevolution of Evaluation Functions</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sigevo.org/gecco-2009/\">GECCO '09</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.06840\">arXiv:1711.06840</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Moshe_Koppel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i>Genetic Algorithms for Automatic Search Tuning</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#33_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Journal, Vol. 33, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i>Optimizing Selective Search in Chess</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://icml.cc/Conferences/2010/program.html\">ICML Workshop on Machine Learning and Games</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1009.0550\">arXiv:1009.0550</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10710-010-9103-4\">Expert-Driven Genetic Algorithms for Simulating Evaluation Functions</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.springer.com/journal/10710\">Genetic Programming and Evolvable Machines</a>, Vol. 12, No. 1, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.06841\">arXiv:1711.06841</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid David</a>, <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i>Genetic Algorithms for Evolving Computer Chess Programs</i>. <a href=\"/IEEE#EC\" title=\"IEEE\">IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.08337\">arXiv:1711.08337</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Eli_David\" title=\"Eli David\">Omid E. David</a>, <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a>, <a href=\"/Nathan_S._Netanyahu\" title=\"Nathan S. Netanyahu\">Nathan S. Netanyahu</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i>Team Omid E. David wins the 11th Annual “Humies” Award</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#37_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Journal, Vol. 37, No. 4</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Moshe Koppel</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://content.sciendo.com/view/journals/sh/6/2/article-p116.xml\">Probabilistic Foundations of Rabbinic Methods for Resolving Uncertainty</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://content.sciendo.com/view/journals/sh/6/2/sh.6.issue-2.xml\">Studia Humana, Vol. 6, No. 2</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\">